M = (np.mean(data[:, 0]), np.mean(data[:, 1]))
N = (np.mean(data[:, 0]**2)/np.mean(data[:, 0]), np.mean(data[:, 0]*data[:, 1])/np.mean(data[:, 0]))

def g(a,b):
    sum = 0
    for p in data:
        sum += (p[1]-a*p[0]-b)**2
    return sum
